## Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows a small house-like structure with the following characteristics:
- The structure consists of 3 visible blocks/components total
- There are 2 layers
  - Bottom layer: A red arch-shaped block (forms the base with a semi-circular opening)
  - Top layer: Two orange triangular roof pieces that form a gabled roof

The spatial arrangement is:
- The red arch block serves as the foundation/base
- The two orange triangular blocks are placed on top of the red base, meeting at the center to form a peaked roof

## Selected Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on analysis of the target structure and available blocks in the dictionary, I need:

1. Block 1: Red arch-shaped block with an opening - this is the base of the house
2. Block 11: Orange triangular block - for one side of the roof
3. Block 12: Orange triangular block - for the other side of the roof

The red arch block (index 1) perfectly matches the base of the structure. The two orange triangular blocks (indices 11 and 12) properly match the orientation of the roof pieces in the target image.

## Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 11
    Step3: Move block with index 12
}
```

This assembly sequence places the foundation first (the red arch), then adds the two triangular roof pieces one after another to complete the structure.
